SKILL|imessage|Send and receive iMessages/SMS via the imsg CLI on macOS.
STEP|1|**macOS** with Messages.app signed in
STEP|2|Install: `brew install steipete/tap/imsg`
STEP|3|Grant Full Disk Access for terminal (System Settings → Privacy → Full Disk Access)
STEP|4|Grant Automation permission for Messages.app when prompted
STEP|5|User asks to send an iMessage or text message
STEP|6|Reading iMessage conversation history
STEP|7|Checking recent Messages.app chats
STEP|8|Sending to phone numbers or Apple IDs
STEP|9|Telegram/Discord/Slack/WhatsApp messages → use the appropriate gateway channel
STEP|10|Group chat management (adding/removing members) → not supported
STEP|11|Bulk/mass messaging → always confirm with user first
STEP|12|`--service imessage` — Force iMessage (requires recipient has iMessage)
STEP|13|`--service sms` — Force SMS (green bubble)
STEP|14|`--service auto` — Let Messages.app decide (default)
STEP|15|**Always confirm recipient and message content** before sending
STEP|16|**Never send to unknown numbers** without explicit user approval
STEP|17|**Verify file paths** exist before attaching
STEP|18|**Don't spam** — rate-limit yourself
PIT|**macOS** with Messages.app signed in
PIT|Install: `brew install steipete/tap/imsg`
PIT|Grant Full Disk Access for terminal (System Settings → Privacy → Full Disk Access)
PIT|Grant Automation permission for Messages.app when prompted
